cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper is about using Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) for human activity recognition (HAR) based on wearable sensors. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing sensor data, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
